vels of formality are expressed through the use of different structures. Given this variety, students of Spanish will inevitably come into contact with variation Spanish. This variation in Spanish adds layers of complexity to the learning and instruction of the Spanish language; therefore, a linguistic understanding of variation is crucial for our students to achieve communicative competence. This unique work, which provides an overview of the most important linguistic aspects of Spanish within a context that recognizes variation, assumes no prior linguistic knowledge and is appropriate as a valuable resource manual for teachers and learners of Spanish alike.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aSecond language acquisition. 0aSpanish languagexStudy and teachingxForeign speakers. 0aSpanish languagexVariation. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / Psycholinguistics.2bisacsh  aSpanish as an international language.  aSpanish instructors.  acommunicative competence.  adialectal differences.  alanguage and education.  alearners of Spanish.  asociolinguistic variation.1 aLlorente, Lucía, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066313608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z978311060671340uhttps://doi.org/10.21832/978184769173640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847691736423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847691736/original  a978-3-11-060671-3  MultiLingual Matters eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014c2000d2014  a978-3-11-066313-6  MultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  